Southeastern Housing and Community Development has donated to WSD29, 200 No Touch Thermometers to be distributed to scholars and their families who may not have access. This partnership was developed to make certain that Scholars who will participate in on-campus schooling have the resources needed to conduct temperature screenings at home. The district is hopeful that this added measure is yet another step to keep our Scholars, Staff, and Schools safe. The district is extremely grateful to Ms. Beth Overton, Miss Alexandria Tobin and the Southeastern staff for their generosity.
#WeRISE2LEADwithEXCELLENCE

post_text:
MESSAGE ALERT:
The Williston School District 29 School Nutrition Program will be offering a once a week meal pick-up for students registered in the Williston School District 29 Virtual Academy. The meals will consist of (5) breakfast and (5) lunches for the week.

Parents/Guardians will need to use email address: virtualmeals@williston.k12.sc.us no later than Wednesday, August 26, 2020 and inform us on how many Scholars they will pick up for each Monday between 10:00AM and 11:00AM at KEES (elementary Scholars) or WEMS (middle and high school Scholars).

Parents with several children can pick up at one location. Please include the Scholar's name in the email as well as which location you will pick up from. You will only need to email us once.

Thank you and you may contact 803266-7878 if additional clarification is needed.
#WeRISE2LEADwithEXCELLENCE

MESSAGE ALERT:
Last evening the WSD29 Board of Trustees gave the administration the approval to begin accepting applications for the WSD 29 Hybrid Instructional model as well as the WSD29 Virtual Academy with the full understanding that if there is not a downward shift in the COVID-19 numbers, school will begin 100% virtually on August 17, 2020. Applications will be made available to parents on the district and school webpages and will be accepted until July 20, 2020. Parents and guardians are encouraged to read the WSD 29 General Guidelines for Opening Schools and the information about each model prior to making an instructional decision for their child(ren) see district and school webpages. Feel free to contact Dr. Shaw at mshaw@williston.k12.sc.us for any comments, questions or concerns.

https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=RTWwo9YhakSkTWbGnfVcKul0Dki_SgZDqgNbyQNMr_BUMk1MUkpNS1VSMFgzVTA2U0g1VFdFN1AySi4u

We are pleased to announce that all of our WSD29 students will qualify for $300 in SNAP benefits to help cover food costs during the pandemic. Please read more at the link below. #WERise2LeadwithExcellence

ALERT - Pandemic EBT (P-EBT) for SC K-12 Students (ALL Williston SD29 Scholars Qualify) Williston SD29 Parents, you can receive $300.00 in assistance. Please read below!
SCDSS will soon be administering P-EBT, a one-time benefit to help supplement family food costs resulting from the COVID-19 pandemic and prolonged school closures. K-12 students who are enrolled in a free or reduced-price school meals program under the National School Lunch Program (NSLP) or are enrolled in a school that has opted to participate in the Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) are eligible to receive P-EBT. For more information, please visit:

https://dss.sc.gov/media/2387/pandemic-ebt-faq-final.pdf

post_text:
The WSD29 Re-entry to school task force met 6/25/2020. The Operations, Safety/Health, Transportation, and Curriculum Subcommittees provided updates. Parent, Student, Staff Survey data were also shared:

Out of 253 survey responses: to date:

51% prefer a Hybrid Model

29% prefer a Virtual Academy

19% prefer daily, regular Face-to-Face instruction

Finally, the group began to review and discuss sample return to school schedules. The team will meet again Thursday, July 2, 2020to preview all draft documents and recommendations prior to Dr. Shaw making a recommendation to the Board of Trustees for approval July 13, 2020. Feel free to contact any committee member for an update or to share feedback. #WeRISE2LEAD üíô

post_text: The WSD29 School Re-Entry Task Force held its first meeting 6/18/20. The team will meet again 6/25/20. The meeting was used for the Administration to provide an overview of: obtaining PPE materials, safety precautions, calendar and school model discussions, enrollment procedures, increasing and enhancing communications, and the issuance of the formal survey to our parents (to be released Monday). Feel free to contact any member of the task force for an update or to provide feedback. post_text:
Hello, WSD29 Parents! WE need your input. How do you feel about your child(ren) returning to school in the Fall?

Please comment with only one of the following number choices:

1. I am ok with my child returning to school.

2. I am ok with a distance learning/face to face model. There will only be half of the student population in the school at any given time. (ex. 2 days in the school, 2 days distance learning)

3. I am ok with distance learning only.

*We are just collecting feedback in order to make the best decisions for our WE family. If you have already submitted your response on a school Facebook page, there is no need to respond again.

Thank you!

A Message from the Williston School District 29 Guidance Department:

The district‚Äôs School Counselors and Global Career Development Facilitators are available to students and families. We recognize that change and uncertainty can be distressing to students and the impacts of COVID-19 can be far-reaching. Please feel free to reach out if your student is experiencing emotional distress of any kind, or if your family is in crisis. We are here to help.

WEHS School Counselor, Alison Brady 803-266-8046

WEHS GCDF, Cathy Smith 803-266-8047

WEMS School Counselor, Linda Mack 803-266-8071

WEMS GCDF, Susie Runnells 803-266-8075

KEES School Counselor, Nancy Brady-Wood 803-266-8113

KEES GCDF, Horace Lamback 803-266-8081

The counselors and CDFs will be available Monday-Friday from 8am-3pm. If you have an emergency beyond these hours and need assistance, below are some resources available to you:

Axis 1: 803-541-1245

Polly Best Mental Health Center: 803-259-7170

Community Crisis Response and Intervention: 833-364-2274

shared_text:
Williston - Elko High School
April 14 at 6:22 AM ¬∑

Reminders:

Google Classroom Distance Learning starts Today!

All teachers have set up Google Classrooms and the codes for those classes have been placed on the school website. Please refer to those codes, log into the classes, and receive further instructions from the individual teachers.

W-E issued Chromebooks back before spring break but if you need one, or if there is a problem with the one you have, we will be available at the school today between the hours of 10 and 12. You must come during that time.

W-E have checked and travel for educational purposes is allowed during the governor's shelter order. If there is a problem with the Chromebook you were issued, you must bring it back in order to receive a replacement.

Remember to check our website and social media accounts for updates and information.

* Fever
* Cough
* Shortness of breath

April 1, 2020 from 12 Noon - 2pm
6th - 12th grade Chromebook pick up time: April 1, 2020 from 10 am - 2pm
**A parent or guardian will need to sign for the Chromebook
**Distance Learning resumes April 14 - April 30
**Please contact your Principal, if you need to make other arrangements.

post_text:
Statistics in Schools Week: Everyone Counts!

Williston School District 29 is supporting the movement to make sure every child is counted in the 2020 Census by taking part in Statistics in Schools Week: Everyone Counts! From March 2-6, this week long series will feature fun classroom activities, to educate our Scholars about the importance of the once-a-decade count. The Census count impacts the allocation of federal funds that schools receive for special education, classroom technology, teacher training, after-school programs, school lunch assistance, and more. Find out more at: https://census.gov/schools
#WeRISE2LEAD

Under the direction of Mrs. Jessica Pym, six Williston School District 29 musical Scholars have been selected to the South Carolina Band of Directors Association Region 2 Honor Band.
Students who were selected by audition will participate in the Region 2 Honor Band Clinic Feb. 21-22, 2020, concluding with a concert on the final day.
Our scholars will work with distinguished clinicians while increasing their musical skills. Williston School District 29 Scholars selected for the Region 2 Honor Band include:
Faith Irons, flute
Cadence Brown, oboe
Gabe Refugia, bassoon (Also selected to participate in All State Honor Band, held on March 13th-15th at Furman University.)
Nathan Causey, baritone saxophone
Blake Garrett, trumpet
Colby Baker, trombone
Congratulations!

post_text:
WE want to take time out to show appreciation to our dynamic trio of School Counselors. Thank you Ms. Brady-Wood, Ms. Mack and Ms. Brady for all that you do and continue to do for our Scholars in our district. WE APPRECIATE YOU!

#WeRISE2LEAD
